#the_challenge.home_sec.container
  .half
    .sub_title What's the challenge?
    %p Refugees often live in displacement for decades, many will never return to their homes. Therefore it's critical to enable them to become economically independent and build a life on their own – in a way that benefits both the refugees and their hosting communities.
    =render partial: "cta_buttons"
  .half
    .sub_title The opportunity

    %p There is a huge untapped potential to create shared business opportunities for refugees and host communities.
    %p Think of co-working spaces, shared workshops and joint creation of new services – doing business with each other provides an opportunity to meet, reduce prejudices and improve livelihood.
    %p In Rwanda, refugees enjoy freedom of movement and have the right to work and establish companies.
    %p.bold So how can we create more shared business opportunities between both communities?

