#home_intro.home_sec.container
  .full_width
    %h2 What’s your solution? Make it matter even more
    %p Do you work with refugees and host community members to connect them through shared economic opportunities, but lack the resources to scale your approach globally?
    %p Do you have a solution in the private or non profit sector to connect refugees and host community members through shared business opportunities and would like to share it?
    %p GIZ gives you the opportunity to work with our network of development experts, designers, and entrepreneurs to scale your solution and make it matter to people that need it most. Submit your solution until [DATE], participate in an innovation lab in Rwanda and prototype your solution together with the local refugee and host community.
    .accordion
      .accord-single
        .accord-toggle
          .bold.red
            =fa_icon "plus-circle"
            Why you should participate…
        .accord-cont
          .half
            %p.bold.low_margin Join the innovation lab in Rwanda 
            %p Throughout the project you will collaborate closely with a team of designers and development experts to push your solution and adapt it locally. In a one week design workshop in Rwanda, you will prototype an enhanced version of your solution with local experts and members of the refugee and host communities. Travel costs will be covered.
            %p.bold.low_margin Access the expertise of the GIZ network 
            %p You can benefit from the expertise and support of GIZ, Germany’s development agency and its network of experts from leading global and local organisations.
          .half
            %p.bold.low_margin Get investment to improve and scale your solution
            %p Once your solution is adapted and enhanced in the innovation lab, together with your new team, you can receive up to 10,000 Euros to run a market-test of your solution in Rwanda.
            %p.bold.low_margin Present your solution to a global network 
            %p You have the chance to see your solution promoted through media, partners and GIZ channels.


#home_why.home_sec.container
  .full_width
    %h2 Why an open call for solutions?
  .half
    %p.bold.low_margin Instead of starting at zero, we want to build on existing knowledge and experience 
    %p We believe that there are people who have solved this challenge before us. Maybe in a different context, maybe with a different focus. None the less, we want to build on these experiences to leapfrog to solutions that we know have potential to make a change.
    %p.bold.low_margin Believing in the skills of others 
    %p As GIZ, we are aware that solutions to this challenge might exist somewhere, created by small or large organisations, start-ups, NGOs or private individual that might not yet be connected to us. We would like to change this by inviting them to participate in an open call for solutions.
  .half
    %p.bold.low_margin Adapting the solutions to align with needs of local communities 
    %p A jury will select the three solutions with the biggest potential, to be tested and adapted on-site to align with the needs of local communities during a design lead workshop and prototyping phase. As an example country, we chose Rwanda. However, the objective is, to scale successful solutions in other countries who combat similar challenges.
    %p.bold.low_margin Pitching to attract investors 
    %p After receiving seed funding from GIZ to develop a first MVP, local teams will pitch their solutions to attract further investment for increasing the impact through scaling.


